From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dueris <duerismc@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 28 Jun 2026 20:25:03 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Region Threading

This patch and its contents is comprised of the following:
- The initial region threading base patch, authored by SpottedLeaf <Spottedleaf@users.noreply.github.com>, annotated
  with "// Folia..." comments.
  - This patch has been modified from its original form by author Dueris <duerismc@gmail.com> of CanvasMC, with
    cleanups of imports, annotations, comments, removal of dead code, typo fixes, etc, of which are not annotated with
    "// Canvas ..." comments, given these are formatting fixes and meant to preserve the cleanliness of the repository
    code. It was felt that adding these "// Canvas" comments for wherever we did a typo fix or import or annotation,
    etc, would defeat the purpose of the cleanup, given we would be cluttering it with more comments for a very small
    diff that is intended to clean things up.
- Fixes provided by CanvasMC including bug fixes, crash fixes, behavioral issues, rewrites of various Vanilla systems,
  restorations of APIs provided by PaperMC that were disabled by Folia, and additions to new API for the region
  threading environment, annotated with "// Canvas..." comments
- Fixes provided by LuminolMC including a few minor bug fixes annotated with "// Luminol..." comments

The licenses for all 3 projects can be found in the directory "/canvas-server/src/main/resources", containing the Canvas
license, Luminol license, and Folia license

Note: The credits shown below relating to Luminol are directed towards the "LuminolCustomArchive" repository. This is to
provide access to the referenced files, given the Luminol repository was taken down by its maintainers, no longer
accessible. The organization owner "LuminolCustomArchived" will be used throughout this commit description to outline
what patches were intentionally derived from, based on, or ported from LuminolMC and it's products.

Canvas combines all patches *except* the "0007-Region-profiler" patch in Folia due to the structure of this repository
already incorporating all Folia changes, maintained as a Paper fork.

The directory shown below contains all patches derived from Folia merged together in this patch:
- https://github.com/PaperMC/Folia/tree/ver/26.2.x/folia-server/minecraft-patches/features

The patch in question excluded from Canvas' repository is:
- https://github.com/PaperMC/Folia/blob/ver/26.2.x/folia-server/minecraft-patches/features/0007-Region-profiler.patch

All Folia-derived sources are attributed with "// Folia..." comments. Credit for the original implementation belongs to
SpottedLeaf <Spottedleaf@users.noreply.github.com>. The code at the time of writing has already diverged from it's
original form through cleanups, formatting improvements, typo fixes, etc, and is expected to continue to diverge over
time. Non-formatting modifications are attributed in this patch file and in-source using the appropriate comments.

For files deriving from "io/papermc/paper/threadedregions", imports added by CanvasMC are added to the respective import
section of the Java class files, not included as the FQCN in the annotated changes provided by CanvasMC. These import
statements, starting with "import ...;" are not annotated with `// Canvas...` comments.

The branch target for the above Folia sources is "ver/26.2.x" at the time of writing. Folia changes will be upstreamed
into Canvas over the course of both Folia and Canvas' development, and the target branch will be updated accordingly.
If this target branch accidentally becomes outdated, whether it be missed when updating Minecraft versions or some other
reason, please inform the CanvasMC team through our discord or open an issue report, and we will resolve the outdated
comment ASAP.

The patches directly and intentionally derived or based from Luminol to the best of my knowledge at the time of writing
are stated below:
- https://github.com/LuminolCustomArchive/Luminol/blob/dev/26.2/luminol-server/minecraft-patches/features/0002-Correct-player-respawn-place.patch
- https://github.com/LuminolCustomArchive/Luminol/blob/dev/26.2/luminol-server/minecraft-patches/features/0022-Teleport-async-if-entity-was-moving-to-another-regio.patch
  - According to the author of https://github.com/CraftCanvasMC/Canvas/pull/164, BaconCat1, some of the code is from
    him, some from Luminol. Attribution has been provided in the patched source variant of the PR in question too, see
    Level.java for the related attribution to LuminolMC regarding this patch.

This list and description of the patch will be updated over time as new developments are made.

